File: The total number of COVID-19 tests conducted to date is 2,505.646 with 33,899 new tests conducted since the last report. JOHANNESBURG - The number of confirmed COVID-19 infections in South Africa has climbed to 373,628. The National Department of Health reported an additional 8,940 confirmed cases in the country. READ: SA ranked 5th globally for COVID-19 infections A total of 140 new deaths have been reported, bringing the death toll to 5,173. The department said the number of recoveries stands at 194,865 which translates to a recovery rate of 52 percent.  The total number of tests conducted to date is 2,505,646 with 33,899 new tests conducted since the last report. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.